# Generated files and directories
/target/

# Dependency lock file (for executables)
# For libraries, Cargo.lock should generally be committed for reproducible builds.
# For executables, it can be ignored as the exact dependency versions might be less critical
# and new versions are often desired.
# Uncomment the following line if you are building an executable and wish to ignore it:
Cargo.lock

